'''''anna''''' is a noun meaning "gift" in [[Quenya]].<ref name="Names">{{App|Letters}}, Note, ''The names of the letters''</ref>

 [[Image:Anna.gif|left]]''Anna'' is also the name in Quenya of the twenty-third letter of the [[Tengwar]] alphabet.<ref name="Names"/>  It is the third letter of the sixth grade or [[Tyellë]], which contains "semi-vocalic" consonants and it is the fifth letter in the third series of consonants.  This letter is commonly used for consonantal '''Y''',<ref>{{App|Letters}}</ref> except in the [[Mode of Beleriand]].  As seen in the [[West-gate]] of [[Moria]] inscription, ''Anna'' in this "full writing" mode is used for '''O'''.<ref>{{FR|II4}}</ref>  The [[Westron]] name for this letter is '''''Yé'''''.<ref>See ''[[Alphabet of Fëanor: Numenian, or Westron, Mode]]''</ref>

==Examples==
* ''[[Annatar|'''Anna'''tar]]'' = "Lord of Gifts"
* ''[[Andor|'''An'''dor]]'' (''anna''+''[[nóre|ndórë]]'') = "Land of Gift"
* ''Eru'''anna''''' = "God's Grace"
* ''[[Yavanna|Yav'''anna''']]'' = "Giver of Gifts (Fruits)"

==Etymology==
The word derives from the [[Primitive Quendian]] [[Sundocarme|root]] [[ANA]].<ref>{{LR|Etymologies}}, ANA(1)-</ref>
